<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-447-463  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 447 463.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE: Work-Group Computing Report  Sept 17 1990 v1 n17 p1(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Wireless LAN: NCR unveils high-speed &quot;spread-spectrum frequencytechnology&quot; device. (NCR WaveLAN) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   NCR Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   NCR Wavelan (Local area network) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionLocal Area NetworksWireless Networks.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NCR Corp. Monday became the first major vendor to announce a high-speedwireless local-area network (LAN) which eliminates the need for wiring toconnect personal computers in office settings.andM;Called NCR WaveLAN, it transmits data at 2 million bits per second (Mbs),more than nine times faster than any other wireless LAN currently available.andO;It is also compatible with Novell NetWare and features &quot;spread-spectrumfrequency technology,&quot; which provides highly-reliable data transmissionwithout interference or interception.andM;NCR WaveLAN is designed for businesses wanting additional flexibility in thelocation and movement of PCs and LANs.andP;  Many face high costs or barriers toinstalling LAN cabling, such as in older buildings.andP;  WaveLAN is also easierto install than traditional wired LANs, because it doesn't require cabling.andM;The product consists of a single printed-circuit board, which fits into theexpansion slot of an IBM PC/AT or compatible, connected to anomni-directional antenna housed in a 3-inch-square case.andP;  The antenna ismounted nearby, such as on the PC cabinet, a wall or office partition.andM;NCR's WaveLAN has a suggested price of $1,390 for the Network Interface Cardincluding Novell drivers and the omni-directional antenna, and $90 for theoptional DES (Data Encryption Standard) security feature.andM;Any number of PCs can be part of a WaveLAN installation within a maximumradius of 800 feet in an open office setting.andP;  WaveLANs working range willvary from 250-1000 feet, depending on the office environment.andP;  Transmissionis not blocked by office partitions or normal office construction (with theexception of thick concrete or metal).andM;Key Executive: Robert James, vice president of NCR's Cooperative MarketingDivision.andO;</TEXT></DOC>